<div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />OK, now I'm curious. If you output the emulator image to the TV, the test still fails. Why?<br /></div><br />If your emulator assumes square pixels, then your video card will just shoot those square pixels straight out to the TV, likely at 7/12 color cycle per pixel, unless you can tell your video card to run in some 560x480 pixel overscan mode.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Jun 08, 2007 5:40 pm</p><hr />
